      "body" : "@PruthviChitrala from the JavaDoc for readAllBytes:  Reads all the bytes from a file. The method ensures that the file is closed when all bytes have been read or an I/O error, or other runtime exception, is thrown. The inputStream is not the concern of the caller of Files.readAllBytes.  <a href=\"https://docs.oracle.com/javase/7/docs/api/java/nio/file/Files.html#readAllBytes(java.nio.file.Path)\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">docs.oracle.com/javase/7/docs/api/java/nio/file/&hellip;</a>"
